fields.title: Spiderman: No Way Home
fields.review: In a word, amazing!!!!!!! In other words, it's the kind of experience that you have to see to believe!!!!

fields.title: Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness
fields.review: Finally a marvel movie that is serious,  more violent, and a bit amount of gore for a pg-13 rating which is pretty good use for it

fields.title: Thor: Love and Thunder
fields.review: This movie was amazing it is a thrill riding action-packed, emotional romantic journey and it is quite funny too.

fields.title: Jurassic World Dominion
fields.review: The movie has great movie script writing and special effects as well as great directing by Collin Trevorrow.

fields.title: Mencuri Raden Saleh
fields.review: This movie was a lot better than I expected. At first I thought it would be a bit cheesy especially looking at the cast that consisted of young actors and actresses.

fields.title: Up
fields.review: This movie was one of my favorites when I was growing up.

fields.title: Inside Out
fields.review: This is one of the most brilliant movies I've ever seen. The filmmakers did some deep research into how the human brain works and it deffinately shows.

fields.title: Coco
fields.review: What a wonderful movie!!!  I really love the message about bringing people together through music and family.

fields.title: The Book of Life
fields.review: In an emotional perspective, wasn't tearful but enough to make you go aww. But in a creative, design, and plot perspective, it's ABSOLUTE ART.

fields.title: Encanto
fields.review: Encanto is an amazing film full of teachings that brings big surprises and great emotions to the public.
